Wits students are protesting against gender-based violence and the recent xenophobic attacks. JOHANNESBURG - Wits students protested against gender-based violence and the recent xenophobic attacks on Monday. READ: Ramaphosa's top 10 quotes on gender-based violence Classes were rescheduled on Monday to make space for the protest in solidarity against gender-based violence and xenophobia. Students dressed in black and purple to visibly align themselves with the #AmINext movement against gender-based violence.